The paper proposes a hybrid model for autonomous driving that combines Reinforcement Learning algorithms with classic control theories. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Machine Learning (cs.LG), Robotics (cs.RO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). However, since the paper focuses on the design of a Quadratic Q-function and the use of multiple simple neural networks for finding optimal values within a continuous space, it is most likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The other sub-categories are also possible because the paper deals with autonomous driving and control mechanisms, but they are less likely to be the primary category.
